File: numerics.info,  Node: Function np_to_list a,  Next: Function np_zeros shape,  Prev: Function np_to_matrix a,  Up: Conversion

 -- Function: np_to_list (A)
     Flatten an ndarray to a Maxima list.

     Returns all elements as a flat Maxima list in row-major order (rows
     first, matching NumPy convention).  Works for ndarrays of any
     dimensionality.

     Round-tripping is consistent: ‘ndarray(list, shape)’ fills in
     row-major order, and ‘np_to_list’ returns elements in row-major
     order.

* Menu:

     * Examples::

1.3.1.3 Examples
................

(%i1) A : np_arange(4);
(%o1)            ndarray([4], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i2) np_to_list(A);
(%o2)              [0.0, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0]
(%i3) B : ndarray(matrix([1, 2], [3, 4]));
(%o3)            ndarray([2, 2], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i4) np_to_list(B);
(%o4)              [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0]

See also: ‘ndarray’, ‘np_to_matrix’, ‘np_flatten’ ## Constructors


