 -- Function: np_sum (A)
     Sum of array elements.

     Without an axis argument, returns the scalar sum of all elements.
     With an axis argument, sums along that axis and returns an ndarray.

     Calling forms:

        • ‘np_sum(a)’ - total sum, returns a scalar
        • ‘np_sum(a, 0)’ - sum across rows (column sums), returns a 1D
          ndarray of length ‘ncol’
        • ‘np_sum(a, 1)’ - sum across columns (row sums), returns a 1D
          ndarray of length ‘nrow’

* Menu:

     * Examples::

