 -- Function: np_norm (A) / NP_NORM (A, ORD)
     Matrix or vector norm.

     By default, computes the 2-norm for vectors and the Frobenius norm
     for matrices.  The optional ‘ord’ parameter selects the norm type.

     Calling forms:

        • ‘np_norm(a)’ - default norm (2-norm for vectors, Frobenius for
          matrices)
        • ‘np_norm(a, 1)’ - 1-norm (sum of abs for vectors, max column
          sum for matrices)
        • ‘np_norm(a, 2)’ - 2-norm (Euclidean for vectors,
          spectral/largest singular value for matrices)
        • ‘np_norm(a, inf)’ - infinity norm (max abs for vectors, max
          row sum for matrices)
        • ‘np_norm(a, fro)’ - Frobenius norm (matrices only, same as
          default)

* Menu:

     * Examples::

1.3.1.64 Examples
.................

(%i1) v : ndarray([1, -2, 3], [3]);
(%o1)            ndarray([3], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i2) np_norm(v);
(%o2)                    3.7416573867739413
(%i3) np_norm(v, 1);
(%o3)                          6.0
(%i4) np_norm(v, inf);
(%o4)                          3.0
(%i5) A : ndarray(matrix([1, -7], [2, -3]));
(%o5)            ndarray([2, 2], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i6) np_norm(A, 1);
(%o6)                         10.0
(%i7) np_norm(A, inf);
(%o7)                          8.0
(%i8) np_norm(A, 2);
(%o8)                    7.649700064568801

